cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AR, cs.DC

This paper discusses a security vulnerability in Intel SGX and proposes a defense mechanism based on control flow randomization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves modifications to the code at compile-time and run-time, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper deals with hardware-based technology, which could place it in cs.AR (Architecture) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
